Descriptive Statistics      -   Work on full data to understand the trends
Inferential Statistics      -   Work on sample to understand the trend and infer the data general for population

Hypothesis Testing          -   Null Hypothesis
                            -   Alternate Hypothesis
    Type I Error            -   Rejecting Null Hypothesis while it's True
    Type II Error           -   Accepting the Null hypothesis when it is False

    Degree of Freedom       -   n - 1 (Total number of samples - 1)
    Pooled Sample Variance  -
            (Deg Of Freedom * Variance of 1st Sample + Deg Of Freedom * Variance of 2nd Sample) / 2 * Deg Of Freedom

Confidence Interval         -